@page "/article"
@{
  ViewData["Title"] = "Article";
  ViewData["Description"] = "Sample long-form article holding page.";
}

<section class="qz-article-hero">
  <partial name="_PictureImage" model="@("/design-system/assets/img-hero.jpg", "", false, (string?)null)" />
  <div class="qz-container qz-article-hero__content">
    <div class="qz-eyebrow" style="color: var(--qz-gold);">Featured Article</div>
    <h1>The Day Queen Stole Live Aid</h1>
    <div class="qz-meta" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.52);">13 July 1985 · 8 min read</div>
  </div>
</section>

<article class="qz-reading">
  <p class="lede">Twenty-one minutes on a July afternoon in 1985 that rewrote the rules of the stadium show.</p>
  <div class="article-body">
    <p>It began, as these things often do, with low expectations. By the summer of 1985 the band had weathered a difficult few years, and whispers that their finest moment had passed.</p>
    <p>What unfolded across twenty-one minutes at Wembley Stadium would settle the argument for a generation. From the opening bars, the performance was less a set than a conversation with ninety thousand people.</p>
    <p>In the decades since, the footage has been studied frame by frame: the pacing, the song choices, the sheer economy of it all. It remains a high-water mark of the live stadium performance.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="qz-tag-row"><span class="qz-tag">Live Aid</span><span class="qz-tag">1985</span><span class="qz-tag">Wembley</span></div>
</article>
